function timezone_bumper(dt::DateTime, bump::Int=3)
    return dt + Dates.Hour(bump)
end

# Test the function
@assert timezone_bumper(DateTime(2023, 4, 10, 12, 0),3) == DateTime(2023, 4, 10, 15, 0)
```

This function `timezone_bumper` accepts a `DateTime` object `dt` and an integer `bump`, which defaults to 3. It adds `bump` hours to the `DateTime` object and returns the new `DateTime` object. I've also added a test to ensure the function works as expected.
